Compound interest is interest earned on an invested amount (principal), plus any interest that has already accumulated on that amount. By paying you interest on your interest, the compound model always outperforms simple interest, which is paid solely on the principal amount. What is more, the benefits of compounding increase the more often it occurs. Interest compounded daily provides a much higher rate of return than its weekly, monthly or yearly counterparts.\cb1 \
